# Vaadin UI Rules

## View Structure
- Views must be in ui/ subdirectory
- Use @Route annotation for navigation
- Implement proper view lifecycle methods
- Inject facades, never internal services directly

## Component Organization
- Create reusable components for common UI patterns
- Use composition over inheritance for component design
- Keep components focused on single responsibility
- Implement proper event handling and data binding

## Layout and Navigation
- Use appropriate Vaadin layout components
- Implement responsive design principles
- Include proper loading and error states
- Handle navigation and routing consistently

## Data Integration
- Use facades for all data operations
- Implement proper data refresh mechanisms
- Handle asynchronous operations appropriately
- Include proper validation feedback

